rComments: All what I can say is: a great lecturer, and he cares! Thank you professor Sayde for everything :-)

Prof Sayde made me enjoy solving circuits, his explanations of the theory part of the course made circuit analysis much simpler. He is very caring and kind, always smiling. 

Thank you Professor!

This guy is one of the few decent teachers, all he needs to teach the concept of computer architecture is chalk and a blackboard! Attend all lectures and labs, ask questions and you will get a good grade. His exams fairly cover of what is seen in lectures and labs.

Mechatronics is course that covers several aspects of engineering, which requires a multidisciplinary instructor. Professor Sayde demonstrated an incredible multidisciplinary capacity, the readings were well prepared and detailed. The teacher answered all my questions effectively and clearly, which helped me to get an excellent grade. Thanks!

I don't understand how this guy is rated so high. He is the worst professor. Can barely speak English, lectures are extremely boring and pointless, and is extremely careless in his test writing. Our final exam had typos in probably 80% of the questions. Fortunately the course is pretty easy so just read the posted notes and you'll do fine.

rComments: This is a really hard course to teach, but the professor is very nice and always makes sure that things are going smoothly. Labs are a bit too time consuming. he is AMAZING and VERY VERY helpful during office hours and is always ready to put in his max effort to make sure a student understands and feels confident. I didn't like BS sequential exams

If you love asynchronous classes, this teacher is for you. He speaks slowly so be ready to speed up the lectures, but if you take the time to listen to what he explains (bc the slides are messy), it's really easy to understand. I watched the videos, took notes, watched the tutorials and had 100%. Labs are confusing so find a good partner. HE CARES

Great course to take honestly; I really appreciated the discord server as it allowed me to engage with my pears more and made it much easier to ask questions regarding content, and easier to get answers, since I can just scroll through what other people have asked. Labs really helped to understand the content. Overall, a very enjoyable course!

Principles and Applications of VLSI Design: This class was great. There was a good amount of questions at the end of chapters where they gave solutions later on. It helped a lot. Also the labs had a good progression and the lectures where easy to follow, complete in detail and the teacher answered my questions really quick.

It was a blessing to have Professor Sayde this semester. His choice to make the course primarily asynchronous made the content easier to learn. His video lectures are informative and well prepared. I especially appreciated how he connected the course content with real world applications.

I took this course in summer 2020. Lovely professor! He really adds to the enjoyment of this course and does the most to make our first remote/online course a great experience. Discord class server was a great idea!

Recorded lectures was very helpful and allow to go back to concepts. The exam is too long for the time given. The difficulty was decent but the amount of time to do just the first question was 1/4 of the exam time. I would have appreciated either a shorter exam or longer time. All in all, Miche Sayde is a good prof and cares about his students.
Reasonable difficulty of material. It was clear that Prof. Sayde really wanted us to succeed and he provided the tools necessary to do so.
Le cours était très bien j'ai beaucoup appris! J'aurais aimé que les séances de quiz aient un peu plus de temps. Mais ce cours m'a beaucoup appris et j'ai beaucoup aimé la personnalité du professeur

Kind of hard to understand, he doesn't really enunciate words completely (just kind of mumbles). So you end up having to teach yourself with the course notes (which by the way are from another prof. This guy does nothing for himself). He doesn't care about students; all marks took months to come out, as he didn't enforce any deadlines with TAs.
